{"type":"message","id":"083efe30","parentId":"21c494c6","timestamp":"2026-02-15T10:54:06.389Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Sun 2026-02-15 12:54 GMT+2] DISK C: CLEANUP & LANCEDB AUDIT (Pro Stream).\n\n1.  **Disk C: Deep Scan & Purge:**\n    *   Recursively search `C:\\Users\\west2` for `DMarket-Telegram-Bot`, `dmarket_bot`, or `.git` repos that look like duplicates.\n    *   *Focus Areas:* `Downloads`, `Documents`, `.openclaw\\workspace`.\n    *   *Constraint:* Do NOT delete `D:\\Dmarket_bot` (our new home). Do NOT delete `C:\\Users\\west2\\.openclaw\\workspace\\skills` (our tools).\n    *   *Action:* If duplicate found -> `Remove-Item -Recurse -Force`.\n\n2.  **LanceDB Analysis (Architecture):**\n    *   Research LanceDB capabilities (vector search, embedded, zero-copy).\n    *   *Pros:* Local RAG for trading strategies (e.g., \"Find similar market crash patterns\"), fast code search.\n    *   *Cons:* Dependency bloat (`lancedb`, `pyarrow`), disk usage (though minimal for text).\n    *   *Context:* We already have `Redis 8` (with Vector Search native!). Do we need LanceDB *too*?\n\n3.  **Memory Strategy Verdict:**\n    *   Compare LanceDB vs Redis 8 Vector Search.\n    *   Recommendation: Redis 8 is already in our stack. Adding LanceDB might be redundant unless we need specific features like versioning or pandas interoperability.\n\n4.  **Output:**\n    *   List of deleted folders on C:.\n    *   LanceDB verdict (Adopt or Reject in favor of Redis)."}],"timestamp":1771152846387}}
{"type":"message","id":"6cd74a03","parentId":"083efe30","timestamp":"2026-02-15T10:54:13.650Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Defining The Search Parameters**\n\nI'm currently focused on the C: drive cleanup, targeting files and folders with \"DMarket-Telegram-Bot\" and \"dmarket\\_bot\" in their names. My plan involves a thorough search to identify and flag any duplicates. This initial step will establish the baseline before any comparisons with other programs can begin.\n\n\n**Identifying Targeted Directories**\n\nNow, I'm digging into `C:\\Users\\west2` and mapping out the `DMarket-Telegram-Bot` and `dmarket_bot` directories. My immediate task is to develop a method that respects the `Do NOT delete` instruction regarding the workspace, even while finding duplicates for later triage. A robust system is needed for this task.\n\n\n"},{"type":"text","text":"I will execute the disk cleanup and the architecture analysis now.\n\n### 1. Disk C: Deep Scan & Purge\nI will scan for duplicates of the DMarket bot in `Downloads`, `Documents`, and the workspace root, then remove them if they are redundant copies.\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"exec_1771152853645_335","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-ChildItem -Path \"C:\\Users\\west2\\Downloads\", \"C:\\Users\\west2\\Documents\", \"C:\\Users\\west2\\.openclaw\\workspace\" -Recurse -Directory -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Where-Object { $_.Name -in \"DMarket-Telegram-Bot\", \"dmarket_bot\" } | Select-Object FullName"},"thoughtSignature":""}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":5190,"output":291,"cacheRead":2317,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":5481,"cost":{"input":0.01038,"output":0.003492,"cacheRead":0.00046340000000000004,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0143354}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771152846389}}
